Job Description
Reporting to the Head of Commercial Excellence, APAC, you will make a key impact in Janssen APAC to drive market leading, insight led competitiveness, customer engagement and the forecasting process through Insights Generation, enabling improved evidence-based decision through Data & Analytics, leveraging both traditional (e.g. data lake) as well as advanced (data science and AI) technologies & methodologies. You will work closely with the regional team counterparts and OpCos to identify opportunities and use cases for Data & Analytics to enhance customer engagement, drive efficiencies and power up capabilities across the region. You will lead a small team that will manage regional rollouts of data management, visualization and data science projects across the APAC countries. You will be supporting the forecasting process and look for innovative solutions such as predictive forecasting.
The core responsibilities of this role include:

Lead a passionate and highly capable team of committed commercial analytics professionals

Build a strategic roadmap for Data & Analytics, including Data Science as a part of Janssen AP’s overall customer engagement strategy;

Lead capability development for data management and data science across Asia Pacific;

Connect AP with global and other regions to leverage and optimize our strategic approach;

Leverage key trends from outside J&J;

Partner closely with JJT to ensure we have the best and most efficient technology platforms to realize the full benefits of Data & Analytics;

Financial accountability and management of budgets, investment choices and planning for the region;

Identify and coordinate resources, monitor operating expenses, and maintain key relationships essential to achieving business goals.

Qualifications
To be successful in this role, your background will demonstrate:

Minimum Bachelor’s Degree required in relevant field;

Master’s Degree in a relevant field or MBA preferred;

Understanding of key stakeholders in the region;

Experience and demonstrated capability to lead projects involving complex structured and unstructured data, unsupervised to supervised machine learning algorithms, and complex automation, data science-based techniques;

Ability to travel up to 25% of the time, including overnight and weekend to support business needs as required.

Further to the above, your well-developed commercial acumen, exceptional engagement and communication skills, coupled with your strategic insight will be critical to your success.

